ðŸ”¹ Project Overview

The Library Management System is a web-based interface designed using HTML for structure and CSS for styling.
The project demonstrates the ability to build a clean, organized, and user-friendly layout for managing library activities such as:

Viewing available books

Issuing and returning books

Maintaining student records

Navigating through librarian functions

Although this version is frontend-only, it lays the foundation for a full-stack system.

